<subsection xml:id="subsec-rotation-in-real-life" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Rotation in Real Life</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction>
            <dl>
                <li>
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p>
                        2.0 Measurements and Geometry
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p>
                        2.3 Rotation
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p>
                        Appreciate the application of rotation in real-life situations
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p>
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p>
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            <p component="lesson-plan">
                <p> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Identify everyday objects and situations that involve rotation. Understand that rotation is used in engineering (gears, turbines), time-keeping (clocks), transportation (wheels), and design (logos, patterns). Recognise that rotational motion involves a fixed centre point and an angle of rotation.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Identify and describe rotation in given real-world scenarios (clock hands, Ferris wheels, gears, windmills). Calculate angles of rotation for practical situations. Determine the position of objects after rotation in real contexts.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Analyse how rotation principles are applied in mechanical systems, design, and everyday life. Solve practical problems involving rotational motion. Design patterns or mechanisms that utilise rotation.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p>
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/rotation/rotation-in-real-life.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/measurements-and-geometry/rotation/step-by-step-guide_rotation-in-real-life.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Rotation Around Us</title>
        <dl>
            <li>
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p>
                    15 minutes
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <title>Grouping</title>
                <p>
                    Groups
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
        <table>
            <title>Possible Responses</title>
            <tabular halign="left">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Object</cell>
                    <cell>Centre of Rotation</cell>
                    <cell>Direction</cell>
                    <cell>Typical Angle</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Clock hands</cell>
                    <cell>Clock centre</cell>
                    <cell>Clockwise</cell>
                    <cell><m>360^\circ</m> per cycle</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Door</cell>
                    <cell>Hinges</cell>
                    <cell>Both</cell>
                    <cell>Up to <m>180^\circ</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Wheel</cell>
                    <cell>Axle</cell>
                    <cell>Both</cell>
                    <cell>Continuous <m>360^\circ</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Fan blade</cell>
                    <cell>Motor shaft</cell>
                    <cell>Anticlockwise</cell>
                    <cell>Continuous</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Ferris wheel</cell>
                    <cell>Central axle</cell>
                    <cell>Varies</cell>
                    <cell><m>360^\circ</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Windmill</cell>
                    <cell>Hub</cell>
                    <cell>Varies by wind</cell>
                    <cell><m>360^\circ</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Key in lock</cell>
                    <cell>Keyhole centre</cell>
                    <cell>Both</cell>
                    <cell><m>90^\circ</m> to <m>360^\circ</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Steering wheel</cell>
                    <cell>Centre column</cell>
                    <cell>Both</cell>
                    <cell>Varies</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Merry-go-round</cell>
                    <cell>Central pole</cell>
                    <cell>Anticlockwise</cell>
