    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>

        <table>
            <title>Differentiation</title>
            <tabular halign="left">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Struggling Learners (Support)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Scaffolding:</alert> Use physical objects (clock, spinning top) and visual aids/videos. Start with full rotation only. Provide formulas. Pair work for support.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>On-Level Learners (Core)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>Complete all three problem types. Gear calculations. Clock problems including angles and overlap.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line><alert>Extended Learning Experience:</alert> Angular velocity calculations. Design a gear system for a specific ratio. Investigate planetary gears. Create a rotation-based animation storyboard.</line>
                    </cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>

        <paragraphs>
            <title>Extension Activity: Design a Rotation-Based Mechanism</title>
            <ol marker="(a)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Choose one: clock, gear system, or Ferris wheel model.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Draw the mechanism to scale on grid paper.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Label the centre of rotation, direction, and angle.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Calculate:
                        <ul>
                            <li>For gear system <mdash/> gear ratios, angles, rpm.</li>
                            <li>For Ferris wheel <mdash/> angles between seats, time per position, angular speed.</li>
                            <li>For clock <mdash/> all three hand speeds, when hands overlap.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Explain how rotation principles are applied.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Real-world improvement: suggest one design improvement using rotation.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

